race.comment: MISS REVEALING (9) looks the one to beat having debuted in a much stronger maiden at Sandown Hillside over 1300m, trying hard on the pace there to finish within a length of the winner in second. Comes back a notch and while there are some progressive types here, she should have just as much, if not more, upside than any of them and gets every chance from the gun draw. SHADES OF STARDOM (5) hit the line intently first up here to grab a narrow second and should be fitter for it, now suited by the rise to 1400m. Have to respect the local yard and drawn to sit closer. VOUCHERS (6) has been thereabouts in three runs to date, slowly improving with each run. There's been market support for him too and he won't need to improve a whole lot to be challenging. HALF SCOTCH (8) was just fair at Geelong but the return was good and she could improve third up. NO ONE ELSE (3)  is going well and has claims.
